  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Admins can now require users to record why an item has been placed in defective status. This affects items marked as defective on Purchase Orders, marking an item as Defective/Damaged on tickets, and when manually editing the inventory item. Admins can configure a list of defect reasons when moving inventory items into this status. They can also assign a default reason that automatically applies when placing an item into Pending RMA status when receiving defective items on a Purchase Order.</p><p>Managers can use the Inventory Detail List to filter for items in damaged/defective status and add a new column, Inventory Update Reason, to track why inventory was adjusted as damaged or defective.</p><h3 id=\"InventoryManagement:DefectiveInventoryReason-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1952251905/Inventory+Management+Applying+and+Viewing+Inventory+Reasons\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1952251905\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Management: Applying and Viewing Inventory Reasons</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932460163/RMA+Process+Initiate+an+RMA+From+a+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932460163\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Initiate an RMA From a Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931116776/RMA+Process+Initiate+an+RMA+Through+Inventory+Fulfillment\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931116776\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Initiate an RMA Through Inventory Fulfillment</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1938030615/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryManagement:DefectiveInventoryReason-CreatingaNewInventoryUpdateReason\">Creating a New Inventory Update Reason</h2><p>On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Company</strong> <strong>Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, scroll to the Catalog section. From the list of categories, click <strong>Inventory</strong> <strong>Update</strong> <strong>Reasons</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1938030615/Reason%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1938030615/Reason%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Inventory Update Reason page, click <strong>Add</strong> <strong>Inventory</strong> <strong>Update</strong> <strong>Reason</strong> on the right side to create a new reason, or you can click the <strong>Edit</strong> <strong>button</strong> next to an existing reason to make changes. Begin filling out all fields for the new Reason. After you have made your selections, click <strong>Save</strong> to submit your changes and create the new Inventory Update Reason.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1938030615/Reason%203.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"334\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1938030615/Reason%204.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Name</strong> - Assign a name/reason that you are moving an item into Pending RMA status.</p></li><li><p><strong>Description</strong> - Give a helpful description regarding the use case for this Reason.</p></li><li><p><strong>Is</strong> <strong>Default</strong> - If this field is selected, it will be the default Reason when placing items into Pending RMA status on a Purchase Order. This reason is submitted automatically and cannot be changed.</p><ul><li><p>When selected, this will also be the default selection in the dropdown when marking an item as defective/damaged on a ticket or when editing an inventory item. This information is not submitted automatically, you can still change the Reason before updating the status.</p></li><li><p>Only one default can be selected at a time. If you mark this reason as the default, it will deselect the previous default assignment.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Is</strong> <strong>Active</strong> - Select this option to show this reason in all relevant dropdown selections. If unchecked, it will be inactive/hidden from the selection list.</p></li></ul><p /><p>After saving, you are directed to the Reason page to view your list. Now, when marking an inventory item as defective/damaged, staff must add a <strong>Reason for Defect</strong>. For more information, see <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1952251905\" rel=\"nofollow\">Applying and viewing Inventory Reasons</a></p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1938030615/Reason%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
